extracted_news.body:
BlockBeats reported on November 8th that Paxos officially released its October transparency report on PayPal USD (PYUSD), disclosing unaudited data as of 6:00am on November 1st Beijing time, including:

- Total tokens outstanding of approximately $158,956,937;
- Current market value of collateral in U.S. Treasury repurchase agreements at $162,719,629, with a nominal position value of $159,529,000;
- Current market value of collateral in other cash deposits held by custodians at $1,944, with a nominal position value of $1,944;
- Current market value of collateral in total net assets at $162,721,573, with a nominal position value of $159,530,944.

